{{coord|12.5195|-70.0365|display=title}}

The '''A. van den Doel Bible Museum''' is a [[museum]] located in [[Oranjestad, Aruba|Oranjestad]], [[Aruba]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.arubaports.com/main/in-and-around-our-port/ | title=In and Around our Port | website=www.arubaports.com | publisher=Aruba Ports Authority | accessdate=29 November 2016 }}</ref>

The collections include old [[bible]]s, works of art, and other religious [[Artifact (archaeology)|artifacts]]. It is named after Anthonie van den Doel.<ref>{{cite book|last=Alofs |first=Luc |title=The Aruba Heritage Report |publisher=Aruba National Commission for Unesco |date=2003 |url=http://awad.kitlv.nl/pdf//UNESCO%20report%20Luc%20Alofs%20okt08.pdf |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64ActJXAA?url=http://awad.kitlv.nl/pdf//UNESCO%20report%20Luc%20Alofs%20okt08.pdf |archivedate=2011-12-24 }} ({{cite web|url=http://awad.kitlv.nl/pdf/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-12-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64ActJXAA?url=http://awad.kitlv.nl/pdf//UNESCO%20report%20Luc%20Alofs%20okt08.pdf |archivedate=2011-12-24 |df= }})</ref>

